{
  "day": 52,
  "key": "day_52_eternal_identity",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "The Messiah’s Eternal Identity"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "The discussion about Abraham did not calm the crowd.",
      "Jesus’ words raised a deeper question: Who is he?"
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "accusation",
        "icon": "report",
        "label": { "en": "Accusation and Honor" },
        "lines": [
          "They said,",
          "“Are we not right in saying",
          "that you are a Samaritan",
          "and demon-possessed?”",
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“I am not possessed by a demon.",
          "I honor my Father,",
          "and you dishonor me.",
          "I am not seeking glory for myself;",
          "there is One who seeks it,",
          "and he is the judge.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "life",
        "icon": "favorite",
        "label": { "en": "A Promise About Death" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus said,",
          "“If anyone keeps my word,",
          "he will never see death.”",
          "They replied,",
          "“Abraham died,",
          "and so did the Prophets.",
          "Who do you think you are?”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "abraham",
        "icon": "history",
        "label": { "en": "Abraham and My Day" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus said,",
          "“Your father Abraham rejoiced",
          "at the thought of seeing my day;",
          "he saw it and was glad.”",
          "They answered,",
          "“You are not yet fifty years old,",
          "and you have seen Abraham!”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "iam",
        "icon": "priority_high",
        "label": { "en": "Before Abraham Was Born" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus answered,",
          "“I tell you the truth,",
          "before Abraham was born,",
          "I am!”",
          "At this,",
          "they picked up stones to stone him,",
          "but Jesus hid himself",
          "and slipped away from the temple grounds."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "division",
        "icon": "call_split",
        "label": { "en": "A Dividing Moment" },
        "lines": [
          "When Jesus spoke about who he was,",
          "people did not remain neutral.",
          "Some believed.",
          "Others prepared to kill him.",
          "Why did his words create such strong reaction?"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you think Jesus meant when he said, “Before Abraham was born, I am”? Why did this lead to such a strong response?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 8:48–59"]
  }
}
